@@ -0,0 +1,470 @@
+---
+name: meridian:review-pr
+description: Diff-scoped quality review for a pull request. Resolves standards from core/config.yaml, runs the quality-check-scoped skill against the PR diff, classifies every finding deterministically via the PR severity taxonomy, computes a confidence score, selects top N reviewers from recent committers on changed paths, and posts a structured routing comment to the PR. Halts ship pipeline (when review-pr.bypass=false) on P1 findings or sub-threshold confidence. NEVER runs full-repo quality-check. NEVER modifies create-pr.
+user-invocable: true
+---
+
+# Review PR
+
+Diff-scoped, deterministic PR review. high-order play, Structure A (checkpoint-capable, multi-agent, confidence-gated).
+
+## Compiled From
+
+This play was compiled from `reference/intent.yaml` by `/create-play`.
+Intent defines constraints (C1–C10), failure conditions (F1–F9), and scenarios (S1–S4).
+To modify this play, update intent.yaml and re-run `/create-play --bake review-pr`.
+Do NOT edit this file manually — it is a compiled artifact.
+
+## Role
+
+You are the orchestrator. You own the workflow. You delegate domain tasks to agents via JSON contracts — never execute domain work directly.
+
+**Forbidden:** Direct `git`/`gh` commands, direct file reads outside the play's pre-flight, invoking `/quality-check` or any full-repo quality skill (C1, C5, C10).
+
+**Agent boundaries:**
+
+| Agent | Domain | Phases | Role type |
+|---|---|---|---|
+| `repo-orchestrator` | Pre-flight: fetch PR diff/paths/body via `gh pr view` + `gh pr diff` | Pre-flight | Utility (exempt) |
+| `tech-designer` | Resolve standards set + bind intent summary; emit `context.yaml` | Step 1 Context Load | Domain |
+| `quality-auditor` | Invoke `quality-check-scoped` against the diff; emit `findings.yaml` | Step 2 Scoped Quality Eval | Domain |
+| `tech-designer` | Compute confidence + routing decision; emit `confidence.yaml` | Step 3 Confidence & Routing | Domain |
+| `repo-orchestrator` | Reviewer ranking from git log; emit `reviewers.yaml` | Step 4 Reviewer Selection | Domain (ranker role) |
+| `repo-orchestrator` | Post structured PR comment, request-changes/add-reviewer, evidence self-commit | Steps 5–6 | Utility (exempt) |
+
+**Domain agent count:** 3 unique (`tech-designer`, `quality-auditor`, `repo-orchestrator-as-ranker`). Within L2 budget of 5 (C5).
+
+**Forbidden play actions (C10):** Never invoke `create-pr` or modify any file under `core/components/plays/create-pr/`.
+
+**Confidence formula (C9, baked):**
+```
+confidence = 0.25 * scan_coverage
+           + 0.35 * citation_rate
+           + 0.20 * intent_alignment
+           + 0.20 * precedent_match
+```
+Weights sum to 1.0. `citation_rate` carries the highest weight because it directly enforces F1.
+
+## Pre-flight
+
+Resolve `stm_base` from `core/config.yaml` `stm.base-path`. Resolve `review-pr.*` and `standards.pr-severity-taxonomy` from the same file.
+
+| Check | Constraint | Action on Failure |
+|---|---|---|
+| `stm_base` resolves from config | — | Hard halt — config required |
+| `pr_number` provided as play argument or auto-detected from current branch | — | Hard halt — "review-pr requires a PR number or feature branch with open PR" |
+| `review-pr.bypass`, `confidence_threshold`, `reviewer_count`, `standards_order`, `fallback_reviewers`, `activity_window_days` all present in config | C4, F8 | Hard halt — list missing keys |
+| `standards.pr-severity-taxonomy` resolves to an existing file | C4, F8 | Hard halt — "PR severity taxonomy missing at {path}" |
+| Resolve `standards_set` from `standards_order` (e.g., `[kb, ltm, stm]` → resolved paths) — at least one source resolves | C4 | Hard halt |
+| Issue number derived from branch name (e.g., `feature/208-slug` → `208`) for STM keying | — | Hard halt |
+
+```bash
+stm_base=$(grep -A1 '^stm:' core/config.yaml | grep base-path | awk '{print $2}')
+taxonomy_path=$(yq '.standards.pr-severity-taxonomy' core/config.yaml)
+bypass=$(yq '.review-pr.bypass' core/config.yaml)
+threshold=$(yq '.review-pr.confidence_threshold' core/config.yaml)
+reviewer_count=$(yq '.review-pr.reviewer_count' core/config.yaml)
+window=$(yq '.review-pr.activity_window_days' core/config.yaml)
+test -f "$taxonomy_path" || { echo "Missing taxonomy at $taxonomy_path"; exit 1; }
+```
+
+**Resume check:** If `{stm_base}/{issue}/status/review-pr.json` exists, resume — skip completed steps, reset any `in_progress` to pending, continue from first incomplete.
+
+**Pre-flight Eval — SE-9 (F8/C4):** Pre-flight HALTs if `git/pr-severity-taxonomy.md` is missing OR any of the 6 `review-pr.*` config keys are missing.
+
+## Workflow
+
+### Phase: Context Acquisition
+
+**Step 0 — Fetch PR Context**
+Owner: `repo-orchestrator` (utility)
+Depends on: pre-flight
+
+```json
+{
+  "intent_path": "core/components/plays/review-pr/reference/intent.yaml",
+  "stm_base": "{stm_base}",
+  "stm": {
+    "input": {},
+    "output": {
+      "diff": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/diff.patch",
+      "pr_meta": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/pr-meta.yaml"
+    }
+  },
+  "task_id": "fetch-pr-context"
+}
+```
+
+Agent runs `gh pr view {pr_number} --json number,title,body,author,headRefName,baseRefName,files` and `gh pr diff {pr_number}`. Writes `pr-meta.yaml` with PR metadata + `changed_paths[]`. Writes the unified diff to `diff.patch`.
+
+### Phase: Domain Analysis
+
+**Step 1 — Context Load**
+Owner: `tech-designer` (domain)
+Depends on: Step 0
+
+```json
+{
+  "intent_path": "core/components/plays/review-pr/reference/intent.yaml",
+  "stm_base": "{stm_base}",
+  "stm": {
+    "input": {
+      "pr_meta": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/pr-meta.yaml",
+      "diff": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/diff.patch"
+    },
+    "output": {
+      "context": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/context.yaml"
+    }
+  },
+  "task_id": "context-load",
+  "config_inputs": {
+    "standards_order": "core/config.yaml#review-pr.standards_order",
+    "severity_taxonomy_path": "core/config.yaml#standards.pr-severity-taxonomy"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Agent reads `core/config.yaml` for `review-pr.standards_order`, resolves each entry (`kb`/`ltm`/`stm`) to a directory path. Reads `spec/intent.yaml` for the linked issue if present (else PR body). Emits `context.yaml`:
+```yaml
+standards_set:
+  kb: ~/.meridian/core/memory/knowledge/quality/
+  ltm: .meridian/core/memory/knowledge/quality/
+  stm: .meridian/project/issues/{issue}/spec/quality/
+severity_taxonomy_path: ./core/components/memory/standards/git/pr-severity-taxonomy.md
+intent_summary: "{1–3 sentence summary}"
+intent_source: "spec/intent.yaml" | "pr_body"
+```
+
+**Step 1 Eval — SE-4 (C4):** `context.yaml` lists the resolved `standards_set` paths and the resolved `severity_taxonomy_path`, all originating from `core/config.yaml` — no hardcoded paths in `context.yaml`.
+
+---
+
+**Step 2 — Scoped Quality Eval**
+Owner: `quality-auditor` (domain)
+Depends on: Step 1
+
+```json
+{
+  "intent_path": "core/components/plays/review-pr/reference/intent.yaml",
+  "stm_base": "{stm_base}",
+  "stm": {
+    "input": {
+      "context": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/context.yaml",
+      "diff": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/diff.patch",
+      "pr_meta": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/pr-meta.yaml"
+    },
+    "output": {
+      "findings": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/findings.yaml"
+    }
+  },
+  "task_id": "scoped-quality-eval",
+  "skill_invocation": "meridian:quality-check-scoped"
+}
+```
+
+Agent invokes `meridian:quality-check-scoped` with the input contract from `core/components/skills/quality-check-scoped/reference/input-contract.md`. The skill runs single-pass diff-bounded evaluation, classifies every finding via the taxonomy, and writes `findings.yaml`. The agent MUST NOT invoke `/quality-check`. The skill's diff scope invariant is enforced by its own contract.
+
+**Step 2 Evals:**
+- **SE-1 (F1/C2):** Every finding in `findings.yaml` carries a `standard_id` that matches a row in `git/pr-severity-taxonomy.md`. Findings with missing or unknown `standard_id` MUST be absent (rejected by skill).
+- **SE-2 (F2/C1):** The skill MUST NOT have read any file outside `changed_paths` and MUST NOT have invoked `/quality-check`. Verified by inspecting `findings.yaml` `meta.diff_path` and absence of full-repo scan markers.
+- **SE-3 (F7/C3):** Severity values in `findings.yaml` are sourced verbatim from `git/pr-severity-taxonomy.md` row for each `standard_id`. No severity is computed or inferred at runtime.
+
+---
+
+**Step 3 — Confidence & Routing**
+Owner: `tech-designer` (domain)
+Depends on: Step 2
+
+```json
+{
+  "intent_path": "core/components/plays/review-pr/reference/intent.yaml",
+  "stm_base": "{stm_base}",
+  "stm": {
+    "input": {
+      "findings": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/findings.yaml",
+      "context": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/context.yaml"
+    },
+    "output": {
+      "confidence": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/confidence.yaml"
+    }
+  },
+  "task_id": "confidence-routing",
+  "config_inputs": {
+    "confidence_threshold": "core/config.yaml#review-pr.confidence_threshold"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Agent computes the confidence formula:
+```
+confidence = 0.25*scan_coverage + 0.35*citation_rate + 0.20*intent_alignment + 0.20*precedent_match
+```
+Where:
+- `scan_coverage` is read from `findings.yaml` `meta.scan_coverage`.
+- `citation_rate` = (findings with valid `standard_id`) / (total findings); if total findings == 0, citation_rate = 1.0.
+- `intent_alignment` = heuristic 0.0–1.0 reflecting whether `findings` cluster in domains relevant to `intent_summary`. Default 0.5 if not derivable.
+- `precedent_match` = fraction of findings whose `standard_id` appears in prior STM resolution traces for this repo. Default 0.5 if STM has no prior traces.
+
+Routing decision:
+- `block` iff `findings.counts.P1 > 0`
+- `escalate` iff `confidence < confidence_threshold`
+- `pass` otherwise
+
+Emit `confidence.yaml`:
+```yaml
+confidence: 0.62
+inputs: { scan_coverage: 0.83, citation_rate: 1.0, intent_alignment: 0.4, precedent_match: 0.5 }
+threshold: 0.5
+routing: block | escalate | pass
+reasons: ["1 P1 finding (SEC-19)", "..."]
+```
+
+**Step 3 Eval — SE-5 (F5/F6):** `confidence.yaml` routing decision is `block` iff `findings.counts.P1 > 0`. Routing decision is `escalate` iff `confidence < confidence_threshold`. Otherwise `pass`.
+
+---
+
+**Step 4 — Reviewer Selection**
+Owner: `repo-orchestrator` (domain — ranker)
+Depends on: Step 3
+
+```json
+{
+  "intent_path": "core/components/plays/review-pr/reference/intent.yaml",
+  "stm_base": "{stm_base}",
+  "stm": {
+    "input": {
+      "pr_meta": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/pr-meta.yaml"
+    },
+    "output": {
+      "reviewers": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/reviewers.yaml"
+    }
+  },
+  "task_id": "reviewer-selection",
+  "config_inputs": {
+    "reviewer_count": "core/config.yaml#review-pr.reviewer_count",
+    "fallback_reviewers": "core/config.yaml#review-pr.fallback_reviewers",
+    "activity_window_days": "core/config.yaml#review-pr.activity_window_days"
+  }
+}
+```
+
+Agent runs per changed path:
+```bash
+git log --since="${activity_window_days} days ago" --format='%ae|%aI' -- "$path"
+```
+Aggregates committer emails across all `changed_paths`. Excludes the PR author (from `pr-meta.yaml`). Recency-weighted ranking:
+- last 30 days × 3
+- 30–60 days × 2
+- 60–`activity_window_days` × 1
+
+Selects top `reviewer_count`. Falls through to `review-pr.fallback_reviewers` if the candidate pool is short.
+
+Emits `reviewers.yaml`:
+```yaml
+window_days: 90
+candidates_total: 5
+selected_reviewers: ["alice@org", "bob@org", "carol@org"]
+fallback_used: false
+fallback_count: 0
+author_excluded: "dave@org"
+```
+
+**Step 4 Evals:**
+- **SE-6 (C6/F4):** `reviewers.yaml` `selected_reviewers` list does NOT contain the PR author and uses `git log` bounded by `activity_window_days` from config.
+- **SE-7 (C7/F3):** When candidate count < `reviewer_count`, `reviewers.yaml` shows `fallback_used: true` and `selected_reviewers` is drawn from `review-pr.fallback_reviewers`. If `fallback_reviewers` is empty AND candidates short, play HALTs with structured failure F3.
+
+---
+
+### Phase: Checkpoint (skip when: routing == pass AND no reviewers requested)
+
+**Step 4.5 — Optional Approval Gate**
+Owner: play
+Depends on: Step 4
+
+This step is skipped automatically when `routing == "pass"` AND no reviewers need to be added. It runs when the play is invoked manually (not from `ship`) and the user wants a Tether before a comment is posted.
+
+When invoked from `ship`, this step is bypassed — `ship` handles the orchestration decision based on `confidence.yaml` routing.
+
+Present summary to user using artifact paths as the review surface:
+```markdown
+## review-pr Result for PR #{pr_number}
+
+- Findings: P1={n} P2={n} P3={n} P4={n}
+- Confidence: {value} (threshold {threshold})
+- Routing: {block|escalate|pass}
+- Selected reviewers: {list}
+
+Artifacts:
+- {stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/findings.yaml
+- {stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/confidence.yaml
+- {stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/reviewers.yaml
+
+Type **Tether** to post the comment, **Vanish** to abort.
+```
+
+### Phase: Execution
+
+**Step 5 — Post & Route**
+Owner: `repo-orchestrator` (utility)
+Depends on: Step 4 (or Step 4.5 if checkpoint ran)
+
+```json
+{
+  "intent_path": "core/components/plays/review-pr/reference/intent.yaml",
+  "stm_base": "{stm_base}",
+  "stm": {
+    "input": {
+      "findings": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/findings.yaml",
+      "confidence": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/confidence.yaml",
+      "reviewers": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/reviewers.yaml",
+      "pr_meta": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/pr-meta.yaml"
+    },
+    "output": {
+      "comment_record": "{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/comment-record.yaml"
+    }
+  },
+  "task_id": "post-and-route"
+}
+```
+
+Agent constructs the structured comment using the template:
+```markdown
+## review-pr — PR #{pr_number}
+
+**Confidence:** {value} (threshold {threshold}) — routing **{block|escalate|pass}**
+
+### P1 — Blockers ({n})
+- `{file}:{line}` — `{standard_id}` — {evidence}
+
+### P2 — Major ({n})
+- ...
+
+### P3 — Minor ({n})
+- ...
+
+### Reviewers requested
+- {selected_reviewers list}
+
+<!-- review-pr:marker -->
+```
+
+Agent searches PR comments for the `<!-- review-pr:marker -->` marker. If found, **updates in place** via `gh api repos/{owner}/{repo}/issues/comments/{comment_id} -X PATCH`. If not found, posts a new comment via `gh pr comment`.
+
+Routing actions:
+- `routing == block` → `gh pr review {pr_number} --request-changes --body "review-pr block"` AND `gh pr edit {pr_number} --add-reviewer {selected}`
+- `routing == escalate` → `gh pr edit {pr_number} --add-reviewer {selected}`
+- `routing == pass` → no PR state change beyond the comment
+
+Emits `comment-record.yaml`:
+```yaml
+comment_id: 12345
+action: updated | created
+review_action: request-changes | none
+reviewers_added: ["alice@org", "bob@org", "carol@org"]
+```
+
+**Step 5 Eval — SE-8 (C8/F5/F6):** The PR comment posted to GitHub uses the structured template with P1/P2/P3 sections and the confidence score. If a prior review-pr comment exists, it is updated in place — `comment_id` matches the previous one. On P1 finding the PR is set to `request-changes`; on `block` or `escalate` the reviewers are added via `gh pr edit --add-reviewer`.
+
+---
+
+### Phase: Scenario Validation
+
+**Step 6 — Scenario Evals**
+Owner: play
+Depends on: Step 5
+
+- **SCE-1 (S1 — Reviewer):** After review-pr completes, `gh pr view` shows exactly one review-pr comment with sections P1/P2/P3, a confidence score, and a Reviewers block listing the selected names.
+- **SCE-2 (S2 — PR Author):** Every finding line in the PR comment links to a `standard_id` that maps to a real KB rule and a specific `file:line` in the diff.
+- **SCE-3 (S3 — Ship Pipeline):** When ship runs with `review-pr.bypass=false` and review-pr returns `block` or `escalate`, ship halts before `merge-pr` and surfaces the routing decision.
+- **SCE-4 (S4 — QA / Determinism Auditor):** Two back-to-back review-pr runs on the same PR produce byte-identical `findings.yaml` (modulo `meta.generated_at`) and identical P1..P4 counts.
+
+---
+
+### Phase: Evidence & Close
+
+**Step 7 — Write Evidence and Self-commit**
+Owner: play → `repo-orchestrator` (utility)
+Depends on: Step 6
+
+Write evidence to `{stm_base}/{issue}/evidence/review-pr/{YYYYMMDD-HHMMSS}.md`:
+- PR number, title, branch
+- Findings counts by severity
+- Confidence value and inputs
+- Routing decision
+- Selected reviewers
+- Step + scenario eval results
+- Comment ID and action
+
+Invoke `repo-orchestrator` to self-commit STM evidence (ADR 012):
+
+```json
+{
+  "intent_path": "core/components/plays/review-pr/reference/intent.yaml",
+  "stm_base": "{stm_base}",
+  "stm": { "input": {}, "output": {} },
+  "task_id": "evidence-commit"
+}
+```
+
+Task: "Stage and commit only the listed evidence files for review-pr with message `chore(stm): record review-pr evidence for #{issue}`."
+
+**Non-blocking:** if commit fails, log warning — do NOT halt.
+
+## Recovery
+
+When an agent returns a structured failure (per `structured-failure-protocol.md`):
+- Read `domain_assessment.responsible_domain` to identify which agent can fix it.
+- Invoke the responsible agent with fix context + the original intent.
+- Max 2 retry cycles per agent. After that, HALT with full failure context.
+
+## Pause and Resume
+
+**Issue detection:** Pre-flight derives `issue` from the current branch name (e.g., `feature/208-slug` → `208`). PR number is supplied as play argument or auto-detected from `gh pr view`.
+
+**Status file:** `{stm_base}/{issue}/status/review-pr.json`
+
+```json
+{
+  "play": "review-pr",
+  "issue": 208,
+  "pr_number": 209,
+  "started_at": "2026-04-13T19:00:00+05:30",
+  "tasks": {
+    "fetch-pr-context": { "status": "completed" },
+    "context-load": { "status": "completed" },
+    "scoped-quality-eval": { "status": "completed" },
+    "confidence-routing": { "status": "in_progress" },
+    "reviewer-selection": { "status": "pending" },
+    "post-and-route": { "status": "pending" },
+    "evidence-commit": { "status": "pending" }
+  }
+}
+```
+
+**Executor loop:**
+```
+resolve issue and pr_number
+check for status file at {stm_base}/{issue}/status/review-pr.json
+
+for each step in compiled order:
+  if status file shows step "completed" -> skip
+  if status file shows step "in_progress" -> reset to pending
+  mark step "in_progress" in status file
+  execute step
+  mark step "completed" in status file
+```
+
+## Compilation Metadata
+
